The paper deals with the formal analysis of blockchain protocols, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The analysis involves the characterization of Markov chains, which is a topic in both distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also involves the derivation of a bound, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
